Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and dice @yellow onion{1}(peeled and diced into ½-inch pieces).
Core, deseed, and cut @long green pepper{1}(core, deseeded, and cut into ½-inch pieces).
Quarter @lime{1}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat. Add @brown rice{1.25%cup}, @tomato paste{1.5%ounce}, @cumin{1%teaspoon}, @smoked paprika{1%teaspoon}, and @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}. Cook, stirring constantly, until spices are fragrant and rice is coated, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @water{2%cups}, @chicken stock concentrate{2}, and a big pinch of @salt{1/4%tsp}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> For 4 servings, use 4 cups water and 1/2 tsp salt.

While rice cooks, pat @chicken breast strips{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. (TIP: Cut chicken into bite-size pieces if necessary.) Season all over with @Mexican spice blend{1%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken in a single layer; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Add onion and green pepper; cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are softened, ~{6-8%minutes}. Season with a pinch of salt and pepper.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, combine @smoky red pepper crema{4%tablespoon}, juice from half the lime, a pinch of @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{}.

Once rice is done, stir in half the chicken mixture and @butter{1%tablespoon}. Divide arroz con pollo between bowls; top with remaining chicken mixture. Drizzle with smoky lime crema. Serve with remaining lime wedges on the side.

> For 4 servings, use 2 TBSP butter.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.